Table A3 is partly replicable. The situation is just the same as that of Table A2. Because of the error message: coefficient loam not found, everything after the line that causes the problem is missing, so Table A4 and Table A5 is missing from the code result.

column8:
1. Error due to incompatibility between Windows/Mac/Unix systems; to solve "/" and "\" problems, I did "cd $result" before referring to file without any use of slashes
2. putexcel A1 = matrix...using filname: error said "using not allowed"

To create the entire table, I had to run the program multiple times with different inputs for values of gamma and sigma based on the calibrated values of sigma in Table 2. For example, if I wanted to see the welfare costs when gamma = 1.25 and detection error probability = 40%, I would adjust the code with gamma = 1.25 and sigma = 2.0

Furthermore, where the values of sigma were 0, I would type sigma = 1e-40, because errors emerge when sigma = 0
